Guanshan Mountain National Nature Reserve, located on the northern edge of the mid-subtropical zone, is a habitat for subtropical and temperate plants and a sanctuary for rare species. Ancient relict plants like the longstipe disanthus are found in this area. About 'Journeys in Nature': Jiangxi Yifeng Series Yifeng County in China's Jiangxi Province belongs to the subtropical warm and humid climate zone, with an average annual temperature around 17.2 degrees Celsius. Yifeng is known as a home of bamboo in the country: nearly a third of its area is covered by Moso bamboo forest. For more: Jiangxi Yifeng Series | Ep. 1: In the bamboo woods Jiangxi Yifeng Series | Ep. 2: Hardleaf oatchestnut (Cover image via screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)